  "body": [
    "Bhai Kalyan Singh was born sometime between 1920 to 1925 in the village of Dera Ismail Khan in Pathanistan, Pakistan. He had one older brother named Bhai Amar Singh Ji and he used to accompany him in his jatha. Following the partition of India and Pakistan in 1947, Bhai Kalyan Singh Ji joined the jatha of renowned raagi Bhai Surjan Singh. He sang and played the side harmonium with Bhai Surjan Singh for a few years. After the passing of Bhai Surjan Singh, Bhai Kalyan Singh moved to Lucknow and served at Gurdwara Sahib Naka Hindola, the main Gurdwara of Lucknow. He lived there for approximately 15 years and was very popular among the sangat in Lucknow. Word of Bhai Kalyan Singh’s popularity and skill reached Giani Sant Singh Maskeen. He was told that there was a raagi in Lucknow who sang Kirtan in ‘bikhre’ raags and taals, as well as partaal and dhrupad. Maskeen Ji approached Bhai Kalyan Singh and advised him not to bind his talents to one location. Therefore, Bhai Kalyan Singh joined Maskeen Ji in his tours around India and abroad from 1974 to 2005. He has traveled to the UK, USA, Canada, Thailand, Singapore, Afghanistan and more. He passed away in 2006 leaving behind four sons and one daughter. One of his sons, Santokh Singh, holds a masters degree in tabla from Bhatkhande College of Music, Lucknow. From 1974 to 1981, Bhai Kalyan Singh was accompanied on the side harmonium and vocals by Bhai Harbans Singh Suraj, who can be heard in the recordings below. Most of these recordings were generously contributed by Bhai Harbans Singh Suraj, who currently lives and performs Kirtan in the UK. If anyone wishes to contribute any recordings of Bhai Kalyan Singh (Lucknow), please contact us.",
    "The following batch of recordings are from Dera Mitha Tiwana, Hoshiarpur in the 90s. Here is a link to their youtube channel for a great collection of recordings https://www.youtube.com/user/sewapanthi"
  ],
